flowchart TD
  A[Trigger: Nightly/weekly batch or on-demand planning run initiated by Process Builder when new dealer/fleet orders or updated capacity/components are ingested.]
  A --> N1[Stream: STREAMS - Ingest orders, capacity, BOM, cost and MES telemetry into Aera data foundation]
  N1 --> N2[PB: Agent Team - Orchestrate multi-agent optimization to generate multi-scroll MPS]
  N2 --> N3{PB: CWB Lifecycle - Apply business rules and auto-approve recommendations where thresholds satisfied; surface exceptions}
  N3 -->|Primary| N4[PB: Remote Functions - Commit approved schedule and slot allocations back to ERP]
  N4 --> N5[PB: Notification - Notify planners and stakeholders and present schedule with drill-down]
  N5 --> N6[PB: UI Screen - Surface interactive schedule and exception dashboard for review and re-run]
  N6 --> Z1[Outcome: Conflict-free production schedules committed to SAP S/4HANA that lower COGS via optimized sequencing and component utilization, increase line efficiency, and improve on-time delivery for dealer/fleet allocations with minimal manual intervention.]
  N3 -->|Capacity shortfall or supplier compon...| B1[Agent Team generates prioritized alternative scenarios; System routes highest-impact exceptions to planner via CWB Lifecycle with recommended tradeoffs and revenue/OTIF impact]
  B1 --> O1[Outcome: Planner accepts prioritized allocation or applies overrides; fallback schedule minimizes OTIF/COST impact and is committed via Remote Functions]
  O1 --> End[End]
  N3 -->|Automated recommendations violate gov...| B2[Hold recommendations in CWB Lifecycle for mandatory human approval and provide cost/benefit explainability from agent outputs]
  B2 --> O2[Outcome: Manual approval path ensures governance; unapproved changes are reverted and logged]
  O2 --> End[End]
  N3 -->|Critical data latency or missing BOM/...| B3[Process Builder triggers wait and incremental re-ingest, or marks affected SKUs for conservative scheduling and planner review]
  B3 --> O3[Outcome: Conservative schedules prevent downstream failures; flagged items are queued for data remediation and re-optimization]
  O3 --> End[End]
  Z1 --> End[End]